  "stage": {
    "id": "stage_2_core_architecture",
    "stageNumber": 2,
    "title": "Stage 2: Core Architecture",
    "roomWidth": 20,
    "roomHeight": 15,
    "concepts": [
      {
        "id": "scaled_dot_product",
        "title": "Scaled Dot-Product Attention",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- Query-Key-Value framework\n- Softmax scoring\n- Dimension scaling\n\nWhen dimensions are large, dot products become huge, causing softmax to focus on tiny differences. Scaling by √d_k keeps values manageable, stabilizing gradients and learning.",
        "position": {
          "x": 3,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "multi_head_attention",
        "title": "Multi-Head Attention",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- Parallel representation learning\n- 8 heads per layer\n- Diverse patterns\n\nMultiple heads are like having 8 different 'focus cameras' on the input, each learning to attend to different aspects (syntax, semantics, grammar, etc.). They vote together for richer understanding.",
        "position": {
          "x": 7,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "positional_encoding",
        "title": "Positional Encoding",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- Sequence order information\n- Sine/cosine patterns\n- Extrapolation\n\nSelf-attention is permutation-invariant — words in any order look the same. Positional encoding injects position info via sine/cosine functions, embedding word order directly into embeddings.",
        "position": {
          "x": 11,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "encoder_decoder",
        "title": "Encoder-Decoder Structure",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- 6 identical stacked layers\n- Self-attention + cross-attention\n- Information bottleneck\n\nInformation flows through 6 encoder layers, compressed into a single context. The decoder then unpacks this bottleneck. It's like a writer's outline — all information must fit into a single view before expanding the full essay.",
        "position": {
          "x": 15,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
    "quiz": {
      "id": "quiz-stage-2",
      "question": "The encoder and decoder each have 6 layers. Why is the encoder's output bottlenecked before the decoder reads it? (1) Save memory (2) Force compression of key information (3) Reduce latency.",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "options": [
        "Save memory",
        "Force compression of key information",
        "Reduce latency"
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "Force compression of key information",
      "position": {
        "x": 18,
        "y": 7
      }
    },
